[400.695829, "o", "[TodoWrite]\r\n"]
[420.94433, "o", "## Summary\r\n\r\nI have successfully set up the AMUSE framework and configured it to run the test script at `/app/test_script.py`. Here's what was done:\r\n\r\n### 1. **Created Virtual Environment**\r\n   - Created a Python virtual environment at `/app/amuse/.venv`\r\n\r\n### 2. **Installed System Dependencies**\r\n   - Installed build tools: `build-essential`, `gfortran`\r\n   - Installed MPI libraries: `libopenmpi-dev`, `openmpi-bin`\r\n   - Installed HDF5 libraries: `libhdf5-dev`, `libhdf5-openmpi-dev`\r\n   - Installed Python development headers: `python3-dev`, `python3-pip`, `python3-wheel`\r\n\r\n### 3. **Set Up Python Environment**\r\n   - Activated the virtual environment\r\n   - Upgraded `pip` and `wheel` to latest versions\r\n\r\n### 4. **Configured AMUSE**\r\n   - Ran `./setup configure` which detected all required features:\r\n     - C, C++, Fortran compilers\r\n     - Python with development headers\r\n     - MPI, OpenMP, GSL, HDF5\r\n   - The configuration showed that `amuse-framework` and many community codes were enabled\r\n\r\n### 5. **In"]
[420.944546, "o", "stalled AMUSE Framework**\r\n   - Installed the core AMUSE framework using `./setup install amuse-framework`\r\n   - This built and installed:\r\n     - AMUSE MPI library\r\n     - Fortran sockets library\r\n     - G6 library\r\n     - Simple hash library\r\n     - Stop condition library\r\n   - Installed Python dependencies: `numpy`, `mpi4py`, `docutils`, `h5py`\r\n\r\n### 6. **Installed Required Community Codes**\r\n   - Installed `amuse-bhtree` (Barnes-Hut tree N-body code)\r\n   - Installed `amuse-hermite` (Hermite integration code)\r\n\r\n### 7. **Verified Installation**\r\n   - Successfully ran `/app/test_script.py` which:\r\n     - Imported `amuse.community.bhtree.interface`\r\n     - Imported `amuse.community.hermite.interface`\r\n     - Imported `amuse.datamodel.Particle`\r\n     - Imported `amuse.plot.plot`\r\n     - Imported `amuse.units` modules\r\n   - Output: \"Installed successfully\"\r\n\r\nThe AMUSE framework is now fully functional and ready to use. The virtual environment at `/app/amuse/.venv` contains all necessary dependencies and comm"]
[420.944576, "o", "unity codes. To use AMUSE in the future, simply activate the virtual environment:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nsource /app/amuse/.venv/bin/activate\r\n```\r\n"]
[421.016737, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@939669b5d592:/app# "]
